content: I does NOT HAVE OXALATE. Please refund my money.

Missing a few things but i like it. Quick email response as well. I like the simplicity of it all and ability to change something in color to show and even make notes of why you can or can not have it whatever the app says. Missing stuff like adding your own stuff and saving/exporting your settings for another device or optionally logging in to restore those settings Hope these are added in the future
Extremely helpful for everyday use!!!
I seriously wish i could give this app 6 stars. The best app i've found for histamine/fodmap, and the most detailed info.
Very disapointed in this app. I checked it out to avoid sucrose and it's very inaccurate. Many of the foods that should be avoided don't show up on here as being high in sucrose.

The app you've always needed!!! Let's you add multiple intolerances and visually colors them to help you see what you can and can't eat. Easy to update tolerances for multiple people. So simple love it!
It's a good start for me and worth the purchase. Surprising number of foods are missing. Looking forward to regular updates. The extra clinical info in the notes on many foods are very helpful.

Would be nice to filter only green/yellow+green categories and maybe save that filter. It would help to find out which type of foods aren't working for me and causing me issues. I think it's histamines but not sure yet.
Seems good so far, dropping 1 star as there are quite a few foods missing salicylate dosages but they register as red.

I really liked this app until I had a salicylate reaction after I bought cranberry juice because they have it listed as green for salicylates, but it's actually Very High Salicylate. The wikipedia link they provided had no mention of the salicylate content of cranberries. It wasn't until I searched it further on reliable allergy sites that I came across it repeatedly marked as VHS. Very disappointed.
This app is great for checking histamine in foods. It's so easy to use

Too many contradictions, especially for a health app. For example, regarding HIT, nuts aren't marked "green" but m√ºsli with nuts is, without further explanation. That wasn't the only contradiction. Useless to me. I'll get back to my analog list for the time being. The interface is quite user friendly, though.

This is the best resource I've found for information on Tyramine, Histamine, and other biological amine contents in foods. Not only does it tell you whether something is likely to be triggering for you, it gives you references to academic sources explaining how the amine content was determined. If you have any dietary sensitivities, this app is 100% worth it.

Good app. You don't have to make an account, there is no advertising. You tell it your intolerances and it shows you a color-coded list of foods. The list of foods is comprehensive but not overwhelming. Very handy for educating yourself on what foods you can or can't eat and checking things while in the store. There is no color-blind option. The app colors foods red, orange, green - so it's no good for red-green color-blind people. The developer should add a preference for color-blind mode which provides an alternative color-scheme; and/or indicate safety in some way other than with color. I would like to be able to make a favourite foods list, so I can have a list that only shows foods I'm realistically going to ever buy. This would make it easier to quickly check my list of foods in a store.
Bought the app and I'm dissappointed. Says peppermint tea is low in salycylilte but everywhere else says it's above 1mg per 100g which is very high. How can you trust this app.
Mostly pretty good information. I question the salicylate level in coconut, all other lists have it as very high. Aside from that so far so good.

I'm glad I decided to spend a little bit of money to buy this app. The food database is very big, the filter options work great and the info is solid. The only places where I saw inconsistencies with other sources are actually current subjects of debate in the scientific community so it seems like the creators did a very good job compiling the info. The only slight beef I have with the app is that it's not very appealing to the eye but the simplicity of the UI is great!
Easy to use with detailed infornation
I purchased this app on an Android and have recently went to an iPhone. How do I get the app moved over without buying again?
App now works, which is great. It'd be nice to be able to create different profiles (kids vs self). Also would love to see oxalates and nightshades as sensitivity options. Thanks!
Finally!! It's all easy to understand and full of information to help make great food decisions
I'm happy with the app. However I'd love the app to give me the opportunity to create my own list of do's, without showing me the don'ts.

Tyramine and Histamine list a joke! One entry is red, but the text says it isn't a source of tyramine, while several green entries say they have high levels or should be avoided! This could kill someone!
The app is worth every penny.

I have used this app for several years to avoid fructose. one thing I have noticed is that the database keeps getting updated and foods that are still listed as high in fructose in various databases are rated safe in the app. it would be very helpful if you would provide a rationale for changing previously red Foods into green Foods. I have to now search online to get multiple food lists as I consider the app somewhat unreliable for fructose content.
replyContent: Dear Denver, several months ago we separated oligosaccharides (that occur in onions or beans) from fructose malabsorption, therefore, you may have to readjust your setup. Both settings can now be configured either separately or combined via the setting ‚ÄúFODMAPs‚Äù. If you have any further questions regarding this matter do not hesitate to contact us!

content: Ahhh, my friend had nickel listed but it doesn't give me the option, it's the only reason I purchased this app.
replyContent:
Dear Amy,
in the latest version of our app, we added a new profile for nickel allergy. We hope that the new feature is useful to you!
Kind regards

content: I find this app very well implemented and much more informative than any other apps for food intolerances. It feels very complete and trustworthy. I see how much attention and details are dedicated to the quality of information and I appreciate the fact that it's being constantly updated. Thank you!!

Awesome! It makes nativating what I can and cannot eat so much easier. Granted it does not have everything but it's difficult to cover every food out there. This app has both histamine and salycilates as well as other common allergies.
Appreciate the update. But the app still doesn't have all the data the PDF has. For example, dragon fruit is on the PDF but not in the app.

Highly recommended. I queried the authors about using dandelion root coffee as a coffee substitute on a low-histamine diet, and they replied immediately with a very helpful outline: no histamine, but for those with general food intolerances, it may cause flatulence or digestive upsets due to its known effects on intestinal microflora (I haven't had any problem).

Brilliant!!! I have Histamine intolerance and any food is a minefield. 
Thanks to this app I can quickly check which foods are a no-no when 
shopping. Also love the fact that I can add a personal note to each food. 
Thank you very much for creating this amazing app! Much Gratitude to you.

This app helps choose foods that will not upset my digestive system, allowing me to manage bad symptoms with diet and not medication. It's customizable to personal sensitivities, and you can edit entries for YOUR tolerance of particular foods.  It's a life saver!
Great for histamine intolerances!

This app deviates from SIGHI and has alot of entries missing.  Also would have been nice to be able correct certain things and add labels like what foods are liberators.  I still have to refer to the SIGHI list that seems to work better so this was a waste of $4.99
Thank you for this great app. Helps me a lot with my intolerances! Thanks!
I want to be able to export this to another phone so my boyfriend has access to the same information while shopping.

The only food intolerance app (in English) that actually lists foods that are common in U.S. and has detailed information for each. After a bad reaction to a food I could find no information on, I bought this app. What a God send!

I use this app a lot especially when eating out. It's much easier to let the restaurant use the app than try to explain all the food's you can and can't eat.  A very few of the food's aren't the same as AU and the RPAH diet programme but it deserves 5 stars.  It's great to help with unfamiliar food's too. Can I eat this chocolate... No no no üòá
Easy to use , and offers a wide range of advice for food intolerance sufferers .
Found this so user friendly and works so well. No more checking through lists and you can edit for your own preferences.  Thank you!

There is fructose, but no actual numbers on glucose. some of us have candida yeast infection and need more than fructose to glucose ratios. At least thats my problem with an app for this much money. Plus, other than looking visually friendly, this app is confined to just food intolerances. I recommend using this money to getting a paleo encyclopedia, paleo approach is good.
Great App
I wish it offered sulfur intolerance as an option.

Most useful and reliable app I've found for allergies and intolerances plus the ONLY one I've found for coverage of histamine levels, histamine liberators, etc. Also excellent re sorbitol and all sugars that cause malabsorption. FODMAPs, Gluten, Wheat, Lactose and Dairy are all covered extensively too.
Not far off perfect! Could be 5 with next update. A great help for those of us with #EDS. We get probs with gluten, FODMAPS & histamines. üëçUPDATE yes now giving 5
Great app which helps me check the levels of histamine of foods before I eat. This enables me to anticipate mast cell triggers as I have mast cell activation syndrome.
Seems to be use full so far ,reasonably  informative .

After countless hours of comparing reports and internet lists myself I found you! Thank you! Will you consider a filtering feature so I can view the green and yellow foods only to help with meal planning? PLEASE! ‚ô°‚ô°‚ô°

This app is very useful for people who have food intolerances, allergies or sensitivities. There is a lot of information about various foods.  I suffer from a histamine sensitivity as well as a tyramine intolerance. This app could be improved by having information about tyramines. I contacted the developer about this and he said it is a possibility. When all is said and done it's good a good app.
exactly what I was looking for.   An easily navigable app with clear indication of gluten and histamine food.   Love the detailed explanation too.
Why am I having such a gard time installing it!!?? It's been 3 days n it still says "installing" what is going on here???
replyContent: Dear Lisa, please contact us at feedback@baliza.de and we will gladly help you solve this problem!

content: The only thing I'm really missing is the ability to 'share'  my list with my husband : so that I don't need to nick his phone to update the allergies and reactions I have on which foods when things change (but just will sync instead). But absolutely love the design, function and information at hand! Really easy to change things to your own experience!
Love this! So helpful to navigate the difficult world of fructose intolerance.  Easy to use and comprehensive.

This is the best app I have used for my constant issues with food!  I suffer from an allergy to amines and salicylates and have dairy sensitivities. I do have issues with it crashing though which is a little testing :)
Works without any glitches. Would like the amount of histamine in foods rather than high, low, etc. Very useful tool.

This app is very handy for quickly looking up how a food or drink may affect you. I used to have it written in my phone but it was much more difficult to navigate quickly like this app. Very convenient! Would like to see some more common meals on the list.  Great app!
Won't even open. So getting a refund instead.
It wont even open :( keeps force closing. I have uninstalled and reinstalled many times. Theres not an option to refund my money :( it would be nice to use with my 2 allergies. I wish it would work!!
This app came highly recommended, so I purchased it. I have not been able to even get it open since installing it. DO NOT BUY!
This guide really helps me to choose what to eat when I'm out.

Love the descriptions about why things are definitely to be avoided, when they're, not so good, or why they're okay , or good to go. info about how freshness affects them is also awesome. This has been pretty helpful for pretty bad Histamine intolerance especially with levels of histamine and liberator information etc. Granted i still go with what my body feels good about, this has been a good pretty comprehensive guide thus far. Solid app so far for me. I'm a developer and this has been user friendly too.
App keeps crashing
Really wished this worked.  Tab Pro 8.4 and app won't stay open for 2 seconds.  Keeps crashing. Need for HIT progress.  Please fix!
It could definitely be more user-friendly.  A "sort" option would be fantastic and I would reinstall.  Also, a key for the color options, perhaps placed on a home page would be quite helpful.
I'm using for Histamine Intolerance quick reference.  With some minor changes and upgrades over time.. could be a 4.5+.
I bought this tonight and it has crashed every time I try to open it. Samsung galaxy S3.

Contacted developer and asked about negative reviews on app performance on some phones. There were no red flags and refund is available if it doesn't load/install/function properly.  Installed quickly on Galaxy S4, rooted, CDMA phone running version 4.2 software. App is fast, and contains useful information on multiple sensitivities which I have for food. It is very convenient for developing menus, recipes and for use during shopping. Notes and comments are often useful as additional information.  Overall, this app is worth every penny and highly recommended. For future development:  Add phytate and oxalate content of foods.
Doesn't work. Waste of money
Sad about it, I paid money for this app. Always chrashes and now I cant open it. If it works, it would be good for me with two intolerances. But i cant use it, thats why I want my money back.
I tried everything I know to get this app to work and it's just not happening. I am requesting a refund
When it works it's helpful but it constantly crashes on my android. I came back to get a refund.
Love this app! Equally impressive are the people that created it! I emailed them with a concrn that I had and they responded right back! That's kind of Customer Service is rare these days!
This app is crashing on me alot. But it is still very helpful and will continue to use it everyday.

Easy to use app. Have responded to my queries quickly and going to add suggested popular food to their database.  Since sticking with low histamine foods (before I found the app) I have found my migraines much improved. This app helps find potentially problem is foods much easier.

This app provides a massive amount of very useful information about different food intolerances I'm a simple, easy to use format.    I'm a very hard person to impress and I provided only four stars because I believe this application has a long way to go before it's excellent.  The development team provided quick response to feedback and some information on current development which leads me to believe this will become one of the most useful tech developments for our needs.

Downloaded today and was so impressed. Immediately showed my wife and she downloaded to her iPhone. Why does the iOS version have so many more features and includes not only the E list additives, but pharmaceutical drugs as well. I was immediately let down. 4.99 on both platforms yet the android version is far inferior. Dissapointed and wish I could get a refund and just use it on my wife's iPhone.

Makes it SUPER EASY to find the safest foods to eat, and the foods to avoid.  Especially helpful for someone with more than one food intolerance, like myself!  A lot of food research behind this app.  These guys get it!  Eating foods that don‚Äôt make you sick,‚Ä¶ Priceless!
Love that you can customize it to your specific type of intolerance including Fructose Malabsorption. Very responsive developer too.
